title: 820-3476 - Missing SMC_DELAYED_PWRGD
message:
Board seems to have been touched by idiots before but I can't find any solder marks, only heat around the CPU (but nothing is melted so I assume it was below 200C)

System has PM_S0_PGOOD but is missing SMC_DELAYED_PWRGD and thus does not boot.

SMC_DELAYED_PWRGD is not shorted to ground

Other then messed up SMC, what could this be? Any clues?

title: 820-3476 - Missing SMC_DELAYED_PWRGD
message: Uhm, are all rails coming on besides CPU Vcore?

title: 820-3476 - Missing SMC_DELAYED_PWRGD
message:
Overlooked PP3V3_S4SW_SNS which is not being created because SMC_SENSOR_PWR_EN is low. Its also not shorted to ground which still makes this an SMC issue.
I've never seen this issue before, any idea why the SMC is keeping SMC_SENSOR_PWR_EN low?

I have Vcore by the way, otherwise there woudn't be PM_S0_PGOOD on this board.

title: 820-3476 - Missing SMC_DELAYED_PWRGD
message: It could be anything, it just means the CPU is not talking to the SMC to release the PGOOD signals. Bad ROM, SMC, CPU, RAM, one stupid missing resistor or cap, something like that.
